VERSION FEATURES:

Voter blocks and ballot preview, fixing of long-standing bugs, upgraded JS, and some code cleanup.


INSTALLATION:

See INSTALL


ABOUT:

Halalan is an open-source voting system designed for student elections. It aims to automate the manual processes of elections such as counting, archiving, and voting. It is designed to be easy-to-use and secure.

It is currently being developed and maintained by the University of the Philippines Linux Usersâ€™ Group (UnPLUG), a student organization from the University of the Philippines Diliman.


DOCUMENT FORMAT:

The formating of files under docs/ are copied from the documents of PHP Timeclock http://timeclock.sourceforge.net.


